### React Component: Live RxDB Data with Signals

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/articles/optimistic-ui.md

This React component example shows how to integrate RxDB's data streams using signals for real-time updates. It subscribes to a collection's query results via a signal, ensuring the UI instantly reflects any changes in the database. This pattern is useful for maintaining an optimistic UI in React applications.

```tsx
import React from 'react';

function MyComponent({ myCollection }) {
  // .find().$$ provides a signal that updates whenever data changes
  const docsSignal = myCollection.find().$$;

  return (
    <ul>
      {docs.map((doc) => (
        <li key={doc.id}>{doc.name}</li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  );
}

export default MyComponent;
```

