### Initialize RxDB in React

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/articles/react-database.html

This snippet shows how to create an RxDB database instance within a React application. It requires RxDB and RxJS. The `createRxDatabase` function is used with a specified name, storage plugin (LocalStorage in this case), and optional configuration like password and multi-instance support.

```javascript
import { createRxDatabase } from 'rxdb';
import { getRxStorageLocalstorage } from 'rxdb/plugins/storage-localstorage';

const db = await createRxDatabase({
  name: 'heroesdb',
  storage: getRxStorageLocalstorage(),
  password: 'myPassword',
  multiInstance: true,
  eventReduce: true,
  cleanupPolicy: {}
});
```

