### React Native Fetch Implementation for RxDB Replication

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/replication-couchdb.md

React Native environments lack a global `fetch` implementation. To use RxDB CouchDB replication in React Native, you need to install and import the `cross-fetch` package. This example shows how to configure `replicateCouchDB` with `cross-fetch` as the fetch provider.

```typescript
import crossFetch from 'cross-fetch';
const replicationState = replicateCouchDB(
    {
        replicationIdentifier: 'my-couchdb-replication',
        collection: myRxCollection,
        url: 'http://example.com/db/humans',
        fetch: crossFetch,
        pull: {},
        push: {}
    }
);

```

