### Signals for Reactive UI Updates in React

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/articles/local-first-future.md

Demonstrates using RxDB's Signals API for reactive UI updates within a React component. This provides a simpler alternative to RxJS observables, abstracting away complex RxJS operators.

```typescript
const todosQuery = db.todos.find({ selector: { done: false } });
```

```typescript
const todosSignal = todosQuery.$$;
```

```tsx
function TodosComponent() {
  const todoList = todosSignal();
  return (
    <ul>
      {todoList.map(todo => (
        <li key={todo.id}>{todo.title}</li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  );
}
```

