### SQLite: Open Database Connection and Execute Queries in React Native

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/react-native-database.md

SQLite is an embedded SQL database usable in React Native via libraries like 'react-native-quick-sqlite'. It requires opening a database file and allows executing standard SQL queries. Data is stored in the device's filesystem.

```typescript
import {open} from 'react-native-quick-sqlite';
const db = open('myDb.sqlite');
```

```typescript
let { rows } = db.execute('SELECT somevalue FROM sometable');
```

